# React Native + Expo — Trellis Mobile App

## Framework
- Expo SDK 53 with React Native 0.79 and React 19
- New Architecture enabled by default — all code must be compatible
- Expo managed workflow — no bare workflow, no native module compilation
- expo-router for file-based navigation (see navigation rules below)

## Component Patterns
- Functional components with hooks ONLY — no class components
- Keep components under 150 lines — extract into smaller files when larger
- Use `React.memo()` for list items and expensive renders
- Prefer composition over prop drilling — use React Context sparingly
- Colocate component, styles, and hooks in the same directory

## Navigation (expo-router)
- File-based routing in `src/app/`
- Role-based tab visibility via `<Tabs.Protected>` in SDK 53
- Maximum navigation depth: 3 taps from any tab to any screen
- Use typed routes: `router.push('/violations/[id]')` with type-safe params
- Deep linking configured for magic link auth callbacks via `trellis://` scheme

## Styling
- Use StyleSheet.create() — not inline styles (performance)
- Design for 55+ users: minimum 18sp body text, 56dp touch targets
- WCAG 2.2 AA contrast ratios (4.5:1 text, 3:1 large text/UI)
- Test on both iOS and Android — use Platform.select() for divergent styles
- Support dark mode via useColorScheme()

## Offline Architecture (3-tier)
- **react-native-mmkv v4**: Auth tokens, tenant context, user preferences (synchronous, encrypted)
- **WatermelonDB**: Violations, properties, inspection records, work orders (relational, reactive, pull/push sync)
- **expo-sqlite**: Complex ad-hoc reporting queries
- Treat offline as a neutral state — never show error modals for no connectivity
- Queue mutations locally → sync when online via expo-background-task

## Data Fetching
- tRPC + TanStack React Query hooks for all server communication
- Use `useQuery` with `trpc.<router>.<procedure>.queryOptions()` pattern (tRPC v11 syntax)
- Use `useMutation` for writes
- Optimistic updates for common actions (violation status changes, etc.)
- Invalidate queries after mutations via queryClient

## Camera & Media
- expo-camera CameraView for violation photos
- Auto-capture GPS coordinates with expo-location
- Compress images before upload (expo-image-manipulator, max 1920px wide)
- Upload to S3 via pre-signed URLs — never through the API server

## Accessibility
- Every interactive element needs `accessibilityLabel`
- Every image needs `accessibilityRole="image"` and descriptive alt text
- Test with VoiceOver (iOS) and TalkBack (Android)
- Minimum touch target: 56dp × 56dp (vs default 44dp)
- Support Dynamic Type / font scaling

## Performance
- Use FlashList (not FlatList) for all lists
- Lazy load screens with React.lazy() + Suspense
- Minimize re-renders: useCallback, useMemo judiciously (not everywhere)
- Profile with React DevTools before optimizing

## Auth (Clerk)
- @clerk/clerk-expo wraps the app via ClerkProvider
- useAuth() for auth state, useOrganization() for active HOA
- Token stored in expo-secure-store via tokenCache
- Biometric login via useLocalCredentials() hook
- Magic link deep links handled via `trellis://` scheme in (auth)/verify.tsx
